"automatically by the Ferraris software. This is done by calling the "
"action ``start_analog_calibration`` (see :ref:`Actions <actions>`). The "
"software analyzes a configurable number of analog samples from the "
"infrared sensor and determines the lowest and highest analog value. The "
"arithmetic mean of the two limit values is then calculated and used as "
"the analog threshold value."

